!ra
Carl-bot BOT 2025-11-14 10:24 PM
Twice per game, Ra selects a target to blind, losing their ability to vote as well as deactivating their abilities that round. This ability must be used in the challenge round, and will go into effect in the elimination round. Once per game, Ra brings the heralds before his court; during the elimination, Heralds are only able to cast their true votes, and any vote parchments or extra votes are inactive until the following elimination. During this round, Ra cannot be selected for voting, and all heralds from the Egyptian pantheon gain a second true vote.

!dhanvantari
Carl-bot BOT 2025-11-14 10:25 PM
Three times per game, Dhanvantari may target himself or another Herald to cleanse them of all negative effects. Dhanvantari receives two vote parchments for healing another Herald. Each round, Dhanvantari bestows a Herald with a bowl of divine nectar. Each bowl blocks one vote cast against its holder. Heralds may stockpile bowls and choose when to use them. If a Herald accumulates 7 bowls, they may enlighten, exchanging all bowls to grant both themselves and Dhanvantari immunity for the round.

Chernobog may store votes he receives during eliminations, holding up to 5 at any time. Stored votes are converted into Shadow Votes, which act similarly to a vote parchment. Once per game, Chernobog may choose to either keep the votes he received that round, or revert to the number of votes he had received in the previous elimination.

Once per realm, Lilith envelops the game in darkness. That round, individual votes are not revealed; only the final elimination is shown. Chernobog may store votes he receives during eliminations, holding up to 5 at any time. Stored votes are converted into Shadow Votes, which act similarly to a vote parchment. These votes still count against him when cast, so he must survive them to claim them. At any elimination, Chernobog may spend up to 3 Shadow Votes in addition to his normal vote. Once per game, Chernobog may choose to either keep the votes he received that round, or revert to the number of votes he had received in the previous elimination.
